WEBVTT

00:00.468 --> 00:02.035
<i> PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i> ON "SECRETS AND LIES"...</i>

00:02.036 --> 00:03.603
YOU'RE
A MURDER SUSPECT, BEN.

00:03.604 --> 00:05.171
HOW DO YOU THINK THAT'S GONNA
LOOK TO A FAMILY-COURT JUDGE?

00:05.172 --> 00:06.739
YOU'RE REALLY GONNA USE OUR KIDS
TO GET YOUR REVENGE?

00:06.741 --> 00:09.641
THAT $25,000
THAT AID FOR MY RETAINER

00:09.643 --> 00:10.743
CAME STRAIGHT
FROM THE MISSUS.

00:10.745 --> 00:12.044
YOUR WIFE IS HIDING CASH.

00:12.046 --> 00:14.113
Ben: DAVE AND I
RETRACED OUR STEPS.

00:14.115 --> 00:16.482
IT ALL CAME BACK WHEN I SAW
TOM'S TRIKE IN THE DRIVEWAY.

00:16.484 --> 00:18.017
I WANTED TO WARN JESS.

00:18.019 --> 00:19.651
ABOUT WHAT?
CHRISTY.

00:19.653 --> 00:21.487
THAT WAS THE NIGHT
SHE FOUND OUT ABOUT ME AND JESS.

00:21.489 --> 00:23.722
TOM WOKE UP,
SO I WALKED HIM BACK TO BED.

00:23.724 --> 00:26.792
YOU WERE THE LAST PERSON
TO SEE TOM MURPHY ALIVE.

00:26.794 --> 00:29.294
NO.
THAT WOULD BE HIS KILLER.

00:42.777 --> 00:44.476
[ DOOR OPENS ]

00:44.478 --> 00:46.645
IS THAT
MY BLOOD-SPATTER REPORT?

00:46.647 --> 00:47.713
NO.

00:47.715 --> 00:49.648
IT'S JUST THE TRANSCRIPT

00:49.649 --> 00:51.582
FROM YOUR MEETING
WITH CRAWFORD AND HIS LAWYER.

00:53.387 --> 00:54.787
[ SIGHS ]

00:54.789 --> 00:56.655
YOU GOT SOMETHING NEW?

00:56.657 --> 00:58.557
BEN CRAWFORD
CAME IN VOLUNTARILY

00:58.559 --> 01:00.759
AND PLACED HIMSELF
IN THE VICTIM'S HOUSE,

01:00.761 --> 01:04.763
SAID HE READ THE BOY
A BEDTIME STORY.

01:04.765 --> 01:07.082
THAT'S GOOD.

01:07.083 --> 01:09.400
MAKES HIM THE LAST KNOWN PERSON
TO SEE THE KID ALIVE.

01:09.403 --> 01:11.437
EVEN IF CRAWFORD
DIDN'T KNOW ANY BETTER,

01:11.439 --> 01:13.806
WHY WOULD HIS LAWYER
LET HIM DO THAT?

01:13.808 --> 01:15.808
BAD-GUYS MANUAL.

01:15.810 --> 01:18.710
MAKES HIM LOOK LIKE
HE'S COOPERATING.

01:18.712 --> 01:21.680
ALL THAT MATTERS IS,
HE KILLED TOM MURPHY.

01:21.682 --> 01:25.751
THE PROBLEM IS, I DON'T THINK
CRAWFORD KILLED<i> ANYONE.</i>

02:16.704 --> 02:18.437
YOU LOOKING FOR SOMETHING?

02:20.608 --> 02:22.374
WHERE'D YOU GET THE MONEY,
CHRISTY?

02:24.645 --> 02:25.878
MICHAEL.

02:25.880 --> 02:29.214
HE JUST GAVE YOU
150 GRAND?

02:29.216 --> 02:30.749
OVER A NUMBER OF YEARS.

02:30.751 --> 02:33.552
[ Chuckling ]
"OVER A NUMBER OF YEARS."

02:33.554 --> 02:35.821
THIS JUST GETS
BETTER AND BETTER.

02:35.823 --> 02:37.523
HE WAS TRYING TO HELP.

02:37.525 --> 02:39.525
BY GETTING YOU
TO LIE TO ME?

02:39.527 --> 02:41.760
HE'S A HELL OF A GUY.

02:41.762 --> 02:44.730
HE WAS WORRIED ABOUT US, BEN --
ABOUT OUR FUTURE.

02:44.732 --> 02:46.632
RIGHT,
'CAUSE YOU MARRIED<i> ME.</i>

02:46.634 --> 02:47.933
IT WAS JUST A CUSHION.

02:47.935 --> 02:51.470
$150,000 IS NOT A CUSHION.
IT'S AN ESCAPE PLAN.

02:51.472 --> 02:54.673
SO YOU COULD TAKE THE GIRLS
AND LEAVE ME.

02:54.675 --> 02:58.844
THAT WASN'T THE PLAN<i> BEFORE,</i>
BUT IT'S A GREAT IDEA --

02:58.846 --> 03:01.914
ESPECIALLY
WHEN YOU CONSIDER CUSTODY.

03:01.916 --> 03:03.782
GIVE ME MY MONEY, BEN.

03:03.784 --> 03:05.384
[ SCOFFS ]

03:07.855 --> 03:09.755
I GUESS
WE COULD MAKE A DEAL.

03:10.858 --> 03:13.859
I HAVE YOUR MONEY.
YOU HAVE MY CHILDREN.

03:15.462 --> 03:16.528
FUNNY.

03:20.901 --> 03:22.568
I WILL END UP WITH BOTH.

03:26.840 --> 03:29.141
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

03:32.613 --> 03:34.780
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

04:01.976 --> 04:04.276
HEY.
WHAT'S GOING ON?

04:04.278 --> 04:05.944
NOTHING. IT'S FINE.

04:05.946 --> 04:06.812
[ GRUNTS ]

04:06.814 --> 04:07.946
HERE.

04:07.948 --> 04:09.481
THANKS.

04:09.483 --> 04:11.750
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

04:11.752 --> 04:13.619
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

04:13.621 --> 04:16.521
JESS ASKED ME
TO CLEAR OUT TOM'S ROOM.

04:18.325 --> 04:20.359
SHE JUST [SIGHS] CAN'T.

04:24.498 --> 04:26.531
HEY, DO YOU STILL HAVE
JESS' HOUSE KEY?

04:26.533 --> 04:27.966
WE SHOULD REALLY
GET THAT BACK.

04:27.968 --> 04:30.769
I DON'T KNOW WHERE NAT KEEPS IT,
BUT I'LL TAKE A LOOK.

04:30.771 --> 04:32.938
I KEEP TELLING JESS TO CHANGE
THE LOCKS, BUT SHE WON'T.

04:32.940 --> 04:34.840
SHE SAYS SHE DOESN'T CARE.

04:37.011 --> 04:38.343
IS SHE OKAY?

04:38.345 --> 04:40.912
[ SCOFFS ]

04:40.914 --> 04:42.347
YEAH.

04:42.348 --> 04:43.781
SHE'D BE A LOT BETTER
IF SHE TOOK HER MEDS.

04:43.784 --> 04:46.518
YEAH, SHE SAID SHE DOESN'T LIKE
THE SEDATIVES --

04:46.520 --> 04:48.687
THE ONES THE DOCTORS GAVE HER
AFTER TOM DIED.

04:48.689 --> 04:50.656
YOU REALLY DON'T KNOW MY SISTER
AT ALL.

04:54.328 --> 04:57.629
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

05:07.074 --> 05:08.807
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

05:08.809 --> 05:10.542
AHHHHHH.

05:10.544 --> 05:11.877
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

05:11.879 --> 05:15.881
OOH, YEAH.
THAT SMELLS GOOD.

05:15.883 --> 05:17.983
IT'S KIND OF BEAUTIFUL,
BROTHER.

05:19.820 --> 05:21.687
I JUST WANT TO EAT IT.

05:21.689 --> 05:23.822
150 GRAND.

05:23.824 --> 05:25.857
WOW.

05:25.859 --> 05:27.759
I JUST WANT
TO POUR IT INTO THE TUB

05:27.761 --> 05:29.561
AND THEN
TAKE A NAKED MONEY BATH.

05:29.563 --> 05:31.563
YOU'D NEED A LOT MORE
THAN 150 --

05:31.565 --> 05:32.631
HEY.

05:32.633 --> 05:37.002
GARNER WANTS TO FLOAT CHRISTY
AS AN ALTERNATE SUSPECT.

05:38.672 --> 05:41.606
IF IT SAVES YOUR BACON, BRO,
WHY NOT?

05:41.608 --> 05:44.743
BECAUSE SHE'S THE MOTHER
OF MY CHILDREN.

05:44.745 --> 05:47.979
YEAH. SHE ALSO HID A BAZILLION
DOLLARS IN YOUR HOUSE, MAN.

05:47.981 --> 05:49.715
I SAY FAIR GAME.

05:49.717 --> 05:51.650
BESIDES, SHE'S PROB--

05:51.652 --> 05:52.851
BOOP.

05:53.787 --> 05:55.587
FINISH THAT. WHAT?

05:55.589 --> 05:56.888
HMM?
I WON'T SAY ANYTHING.

05:56.890 --> 05:58.357
COME ON, MAN. WHAT?

05:58.359 --> 06:00.058
[ SIGHS ]

06:00.060 --> 06:01.893
I KNOW HOW THIS GOES DOWN,
ALL RIGHT?

06:01.895 --> 06:03.962
I'M NOT GETTING CAUGHT
IN THIS TRAP.

06:03.964 --> 06:05.997
YOU OBVIOUSLY
WANT TO SAY SOMETHING.

06:05.999 --> 06:07.599
SAY IT.

06:10.637 --> 06:12.070
COME ON, DAVE.

06:14.708 --> 06:16.842
I KNOW HOW THIS WORKS,
OKAY?

06:16.844 --> 06:18.944
I TRASH CHRISTY TONIGHT,
YOU GET BACK WITH HER TOMORROW.

06:18.946 --> 06:20.979
WE'RE NOT
GETTING BACK TOGETHER.

06:20.981 --> 06:22.547
OUR MARRIAGE IS OVER.

06:27.421 --> 06:28.737
OKAY, JUST...

06:28.738 --> 06:30.054
JUST REMEMBER
THAT YOU<i> MADE</i> ME SAY THIS.

06:30.057 --> 06:31.957
OKAY.

06:31.959 --> 06:34.926
OKAY, DON'T YOU THINK
THAT IT'S A LITTLE WEIRD

06:34.928 --> 06:36.461
THAT CHRISTY WAS<i> SO</i> EAGER

06:36.463 --> 06:39.097
TO HELP OUT ANDREA
WITH THE INVESTIGATION?

06:39.099 --> 06:40.565
"ANDREA" NOW?

06:40.567 --> 06:42.100
IT WAS
A VERY EXPENSIVE MEAL.

06:42.102 --> 06:46.405
LOOK, THE FACT IS
THAT CHRISTY BASICALLY TOLD HER

06:46.407 --> 06:48.507
EXACTLY WHERE
TO FIND THE FLASHLIGHT.

06:48.509 --> 06:49.808
SHE TOLD<i> MICHAEL.</i>

06:49.810 --> 06:52.778
WHO SHE KNEW
WOULD GO STRAIGHT TO THE COPS.

06:52.780 --> 06:55.914
PLUS, THE SAME NIGHT THAT
YOU TALKED TO HER ABOUT JESS,

06:55.916 --> 06:59.551
THAT IS THE SAME NIGHT
THAT TOMMY ENDED UP DEAD.

06:59.553 --> 07:00.986
WAIT, MAN.

07:00.988 --> 07:04.022
Y-Y-YOU CAN'T SERIOUSLY THINK
THAT CHRISTY --

07:04.024 --> 07:05.824
A WOMAN SCORNED, BROTHER.

07:05.826 --> 07:08.560
SHE'S A LOT OF THINGS,
BUT SHE WOULDN'T HURT TOM.

07:08.562 --> 07:11.630
YEAH, YOU DIDN'T THINK
SHE'D HIDE MONEY IN
YOUR HOUSE, EITHER...

07:11.632 --> 07:12.931
TAKE THE KIDS...

07:12.933 --> 07:15.200
DO THE HOKEY POKEY
WITH A CLIENT.

07:15.202 --> 07:17.068
COME ON.

07:17.070 --> 07:20.005
THEN WHY'D SHE PUT
THE FLASHLIGHT BACK IN MY TRUCK?

07:20.007 --> 07:21.540
TO FRAME YOU.

07:23.076 --> 07:24.643
AND AFTER SHE FRAMED ME,

07:24.645 --> 07:26.745
WHY DID SHE PAY MY LAWYER
25 GRAND?

07:26.747 --> 07:28.713
IMAGE IS EVERYTHING
TO HER, MAN.

07:28.715 --> 07:31.283
I'M SORRY.

07:31.284 --> 07:33.852
SO SHE PAYS OFF GARNER
TO LOOK LIKE THE DEVOTED MARTYR

07:33.854 --> 07:36.688
WHO WOULD STICK WITH HER HUSBAND
NO MATTER WHAT.

07:36.690 --> 07:38.223
[ SIGHS ]

07:38.225 --> 07:40.692
I KNOW IT'S MESSED UP.
IT'S MESSED UP.

07:40.694 --> 07:42.527
BUT YOU CAN'T IGNORE
THE FACTS HERE.

07:42.529 --> 07:44.746
TOMMY'S DEAD,

07:44.747 --> 07:46.964
AND CHRISTY HAD THE MOTIVE
<i> AND</i> THE OPPORTUNITY.

08:03.150 --> 08:04.916
YOU BELLOWED?

08:04.918 --> 08:06.852
I NEED HARD EVIDENCE
TO MAKE AN ARREST.

08:06.854 --> 08:09.621
TOM MURPHY WAS ATTACKED
WITH A FLASHLIGHT.

08:09.623 --> 08:11.556
WHERE IS
MY SPATTER ANALYSIS?

08:11.558 --> 08:14.226
IN THE LAB,
WAITING TO BE REPROCESSED.

08:14.228 --> 08:15.961
YOU GOT EXTRA PERSONNEL
AND EQUIPMENT

08:15.963 --> 08:18.930
TO HELP YOU FIX
WHAT LINDA FREEMAN BROKE.

08:18.932 --> 08:19.965
WHAT'S THE HOLDUP?

08:19.967 --> 08:23.835
I GET MY MARCHING ORDERS
FROM THE INSPECTOR GENERAL.

08:23.837 --> 08:25.570
HE TELLS ME
WHAT'S IMPORTANT.

08:25.572 --> 08:27.038
I'VE ALREADY RECONFIRMED

08:27.040 --> 08:29.007
THE MAKE AND MODEL
OF THE FLASHLIGHT,

08:29.009 --> 08:30.909
AS WELL AS THE BRAND
AND THE ITEM NUMBER

08:30.911 --> 08:32.143
OF THE KILLER'S
BLUE JACKET.

08:32.145 --> 08:33.612
YOU'RE WELCOME.

08:33.614 --> 08:35.514
HOW LONG IS IT GONNA BE?

08:36.517 --> 08:37.849
HOW ABOUT THIS?

08:37.851 --> 08:40.085
I'LL CALL YOU
WHEN I'M DONE.

08:44.258 --> 08:45.891
[ DOOR OPENS ]

08:45.893 --> 08:47.559
DAD?

08:47.561 --> 08:48.894
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

08:50.998 --> 08:52.631
HOW'D YOU GUYS
GET HERE?

08:54.034 --> 08:55.267
HEY, DAD.
HEY, HON.

08:57.070 --> 08:58.787
IS YOUR MOTHER HERE?

08:58.788 --> 09:00.505
UNCLE MICHAEL BROUGHT US
TO GET MORE CLOTHES.

09:00.507 --> 09:02.140
MOM'S OUT SOMEWHERE.

09:02.142 --> 09:04.876
WITH SAM.
I THINK HE'S HER BOYFRIEND.

09:04.878 --> 09:06.978
SHUT UP, ABBY.

09:06.980 --> 09:08.680
HE'S BEEN AROUND
LIKE TWICE.

09:08.682 --> 09:09.915
HE'S A TOOL.

09:09.917 --> 09:11.650
IT'S OKAY.

09:11.652 --> 09:12.851
NO, IT'S NOT.

09:12.853 --> 09:15.587
IF YOU AND MOM SPLIT UP,
WHAT ARE WE GONNA DO?

09:15.589 --> 09:17.889
W-WHERE ARE WE GONNA LIVE?

09:17.891 --> 09:19.724
WE'LL FIGURE IT OUT.

09:19.726 --> 09:21.126
IT'S NOT SOMETHING
YOU SHOULD HAVE TO WORRY ABOUT.

09:21.128 --> 09:25.063
YOU'LL HAVE TWO HOMES
WITH NO FIGHTING. I PROMISE.

09:25.065 --> 09:26.698
ARE YOU GONNA BE
WITH JESS?

09:26.700 --> 09:28.967
WHAT? NO.

09:28.969 --> 09:30.635
ABBY,
WHERE DID YOU HEAR THAT?

09:30.637 --> 09:32.704
UNCLE MICHAEL.

09:32.706 --> 09:34.005
HE SAID YOU LOVE HER.

09:34.007 --> 09:35.173
[ SIGHS ]

09:35.175 --> 09:37.842
I...LIKE JESS.
WE<i> ALL</i> DO.

09:37.844 --> 09:39.294
SHE'S OUR NEIGHBOR,

09:39.295 --> 09:40.745
AND SHE'S GOING THROUGH
A TOUGH TIME.

09:40.747 --> 09:42.080
I --

09:42.082 --> 09:43.214
WE GET IT.

09:43.216 --> 09:45.183
COME ON, ABBY.
LET'S GET OUR STUFF.

09:53.594 --> 09:55.694
HEY, MAN,
YOU DON'T HAVE TO RESPECT ME.

09:55.696 --> 09:57.128
BUT IF YOU BADMOUTH ME
TO MY GIRLS AGAIN,

09:57.130 --> 09:58.163
WE'RE GONNA HAVE A PROBLEM.

09:58.165 --> 09:59.864
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

09:59.866 --> 10:01.233
JESS.

10:01.234 --> 10:02.601
STOP PUTTING IDEAS
IN THEIR HEADS.

10:02.603 --> 10:04.936
WE'RE NOT TOGETHER.
GOT IT?

10:04.938 --> 10:06.738
[ Sighing ] OH, BOY.

10:06.740 --> 10:08.707
YEAH,
THEY MUST HAVE OVERHEARD.

10:08.709 --> 10:11.276
YOU KNOW, MICHAEL, I REALLY
THOUGHT YOU LOVED MY GIRLS.

10:11.278 --> 10:12.978
AFTER EVERYTHING
THEY'VE BEEN THROUGH,

10:12.980 --> 10:14.245
WHY WOULD YOU WANT
TO HURT THEM MORE?

10:14.247 --> 10:15.246
I'M SORRY.

10:15.248 --> 10:16.281
[ DOOR OPENS ]

10:16.283 --> 10:17.749
IT WON'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

10:17.751 --> 10:19.017
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

10:19.019 --> 10:20.385
HEY, GIRLS.

10:20.387 --> 10:22.053
YOU READY?
Natalie: YEP.

10:25.692 --> 10:27.859
[ TRUNK LID OPENS ]

10:27.861 --> 10:29.160
THANK YOU.

10:29.162 --> 10:30.161
ABBY?

10:30.163 --> 10:31.930
I'M NOT GOING.

10:33.867 --> 10:34.966
WE DIDN'T GET CHRISTMAS.

10:34.968 --> 10:37.035
CAN WE AT LEAST
GO TO THE FIREWORKS,

10:37.037 --> 10:39.037
LIKE WE DO EVERY YEAR?

10:39.039 --> 10:41.106
I KNOW IT'S HARD, HON.

10:41.942 --> 10:44.943
ABBY,
GO TO THE FIREWORKS.

10:44.945 --> 10:46.044
MAKE A NIGHT OF IT.

10:46.046 --> 10:47.846
YES!

10:48.315 --> 10:49.881
ALL RIGHT,
JUST, UH, TELL CHRISTY

10:49.883 --> 10:51.016
I'LL BRING THE GIRLS BACK
AFTER.

10:51.018 --> 10:53.502
WON'T BE A PROBLEM.

10:53.503 --> 10:55.987
I'LL PASS. NONE OF MY FRIENDS
WILL BE THERE ANYWAY.

10:55.989 --> 10:57.288
COME ON.

10:57.290 --> 10:58.289
Abby needs you, Dad.

10:58.291 --> 10:59.691
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

10:59.693 --> 11:01.359
HAVE A GOOD TIME.

11:01.361 --> 11:04.095
GUESS IT'S JUST
YOU AND ME.

11:04.097 --> 11:06.898
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

11:09.970 --> 11:11.002
I'M EXCITED.

11:11.004 --> 11:12.237
HERE IT IS.

11:13.907 --> 11:15.974
I DIDN'T GET TO SEE YOU,
SO...

11:15.976 --> 11:17.108
MERRY CHRISTMAS, DAD.

11:17.110 --> 11:19.244
I WRAPPED IT MYSELF.

11:19.246 --> 11:20.245
YOU DID?

11:20.247 --> 11:22.213
BETTER THAN<i> I</i> CAN DO.

11:22.215 --> 11:24.149
THE BEST PART
IS TEARING IT OPEN.

11:24.151 --> 11:26.017
I DON'T WANT
TO MESS IT UP.

11:26.019 --> 11:27.419
[ PAPER RUSTLES ]

11:35.162 --> 11:36.961
THANK YOU, ABBY.

11:36.963 --> 11:38.897
I LOVE IT.

11:38.899 --> 11:41.199
YOU CAN ADD MORE PHOTOS
WHENEVER YOU WANT.

11:43.870 --> 11:45.303
I DON'T WANT YOU
TO BE ALONE.

11:47.007 --> 11:48.940
SWEETIE, I'M NOT ALONE.

11:48.942 --> 11:51.910
I HAVE YOU AND NAT.

11:54.981 --> 11:58.083
HONEY, I'M SO SORRY
ABOUT ALL THIS.

11:58.085 --> 12:00.018
BUT YOU HAVE TO REMEMBER --
NO MATTER WHAT,

12:00.020 --> 12:02.320
YOUR MOTHER AND I
BOTH LOVE YOU VERY MUCH.

12:02.322 --> 12:04.055
I KNOW THAT.

12:04.057 --> 12:07.459
IT MEANS YOU DON'T HAVE TO
PICK SIDES OR PLAY FAVORITES.

12:07.461 --> 12:09.894
I CAN'T HELP IT.
I'M A DADDY'S GIRL.

12:09.896 --> 12:11.262
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:11.264 --> 12:13.198
IS THAT OKAY?

12:13.200 --> 12:14.999
COME HERE.

12:22.042 --> 12:24.142
WHY ARE WE HERE AGAIN?

12:24.144 --> 12:26.010
I'M STARTING OVER.

12:29.082 --> 12:31.883
I GOT A BACKLOG OF EVIDENCE
TO PROCESS.

12:31.885 --> 12:34.052
[ WATER RUSHING ]

12:36.990 --> 12:39.791
IF I'M RIGHT,
WE'LL HAVE MORE SOON.

13:19.966 --> 13:21.966
I NEED
AN EVIDENCE MARKER.

13:23.537 --> 13:25.303
[ GRUNTS ]

13:36.917 --> 13:38.950
[ CAMERA CLICKS ]

13:42.122 --> 13:44.088
[ CAMERA CLICKS ]

13:54.935 --> 13:58.203
IT'S BEEN WEEKS.
THAT COULD BE ANYONE'S TOY.

13:58.205 --> 14:01.372
AND THIS COULD BE
ANYONE'S JOB.

14:01.374 --> 14:05.543
I WANT YOU TO SPRAY
THIS WHOLE AREA DOWN.

14:05.545 --> 14:06.945
THE CRIME SCENE
IS BACK THERE.

14:06.947 --> 14:08.379
WASN'T SUPPOSED TO BE.

14:11.918 --> 14:12.984
ALL RIGHT.

14:19.426 --> 14:22.427
TOM'S KILLER WANTED
TO GET HIM DOWN TO THE RIVER

14:22.429 --> 14:24.028
SO HE'D DROWN.

14:24.030 --> 14:26.064
THE BOY COULDN'T SWIM.

14:30.971 --> 14:32.136
WHOA.

14:34.040 --> 14:36.474
HE TRIED TO RUN AWAY,
AND THAT'S WHY HE GOT HIT.

14:36.476 --> 14:38.376
THE FIRST BLOW
HAPPENED HERE,

14:38.378 --> 14:41.579
AND THEN SHE CHASED HIM
BACK THERE, WHERE HE DIED.

14:41.581 --> 14:43.081
"SHE"?

14:43.083 --> 14:45.884
WATER KILLING
IS A<i> FEMALE'S</i> M.O.

14:45.886 --> 14:48.653
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
LOOKING AT BEN CRAWFORD.

14:48.655 --> 14:50.355
NOT ANYMORE.

14:50.357 --> 14:52.056
TOM'S KILLER IS FEMALE.

14:57.264 --> 14:59.030
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

14:59.032 --> 15:02.166
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

15:07.908 --> 15:09.240
[ CAR DOOR OPENS ]

15:10.510 --> 15:11.542
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

15:13.380 --> 15:14.579
WHAT YOU GOT THERE,
MONK?

15:14.581 --> 15:15.947
[ ENGINE SPUTTERS ]

15:15.949 --> 15:17.382
ARE YOU HIDING
SOMETHING?

15:20.954 --> 15:23.187
MOM SAID
NOT TO SHOW YOU.

15:23.189 --> 15:25.189
SHE SAID YOU'D BE MAD
'CAUSE IT'S JUST FROM HER.

15:25.191 --> 15:28.126
[ ENGINE SPUTTERS ]

15:28.128 --> 15:31.996
DON'T HIDE ANYTHING
FROM ME -- EVER.

15:31.998 --> 15:33.631
BUT I<i> AM</i> JEALOUS.

15:33.633 --> 15:35.133
BETTER PHONE THAN MINE.

15:35.135 --> 15:37.001
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ ENGINE SPUTTERS ]

15:37.003 --> 15:38.236
SO, PUT MY NUMBER
IN THERE.

15:38.238 --> 15:41.005
[ CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

15:41.007 --> 15:42.407
Jess: HEY.

15:42.409 --> 15:44.208
MY CAR WON'T START.

15:44.210 --> 15:45.977
WHERE YOU HEADED?
YOU NEED A LIFT?

15:45.979 --> 15:47.378
TO THE FIREWORKS.

15:47.380 --> 15:48.513
US TOO.

15:48.515 --> 15:49.981
YOU WERE GONNA GO ALONE?

15:49.983 --> 15:52.283
WELL, I USED TO TAKE TOM
EVERY YEAR.

15:52.285 --> 15:53.952
IT WAS OUR TRADITION.

15:53.954 --> 15:55.737
HE LOVED HOW LOUD IT GOT.

15:55.738 --> 15:57.521
[ CHUCKLES ]
SHE USED TO HATE THE NOISE.

15:57.524 --> 15:59.424
YOU REMEMBER?

15:59.426 --> 16:02.193
YOU'D MAKE US TAKE YOU, AND THEN
YOU'D CRY THE WHOLE TIME.

16:02.195 --> 16:03.194
Dad.

16:03.196 --> 16:05.263
I KNOW --
YOU LOVE IT NOW.

16:05.265 --> 16:08.232
AND I DON'T WANT TO MISS IT,
SO CAN WE GO?

16:08.234 --> 16:11.536
WELL, YOU SURE THIS IS OKAY --
ME COMING ALONG?

16:12.472 --> 16:15.073
WHY WOULD YOU WANT
TO GO ANYWHERE THAT
REMINDS YOU OF TOM?

16:15.742 --> 16:17.208
ABBY.

16:17.210 --> 16:19.477
I JUST MEAN...

16:19.479 --> 16:22.280
DOESN'T IT MAKE YOU SAD?

16:22.281 --> 16:25.082
ACTUALLY, IT'S NICE REMEMBERING
THINGS THAT MADE HIM HAPPY.

16:27.687 --> 16:29.287
LET'S GO.

16:38.198 --> 16:39.630
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

17:07.727 --> 17:09.727
Abby: HOW MANY TICKETS
DO WE HAVE LEFT?

17:09.729 --> 17:11.763
Ben: ENOUGH FOR A RIDE
OR SOME GAMES.

17:11.765 --> 17:13.197
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

17:13.199 --> 17:15.366
REMEMBER WHEN I MADE NAT
TAKE ME ON THIS?

17:15.368 --> 17:18.336
RIGHT BEFORE YOU THREW UP
YOUR COTTON CANDY ALL OVER HER?

17:18.338 --> 17:20.038
THAT TIME?
[ LAUGHS ]

17:20.040 --> 17:21.439
GOOD TIMES.

17:21.441 --> 17:22.673
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:22.675 --> 17:24.776
[ PEOPLE SCREAMING ]

17:24.778 --> 17:26.744
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:26.746 --> 17:29.414
[ BELL CLANGS ]

17:29.416 --> 17:32.250
SHOULD WE<i> ALL</i> GO ON?

17:32.252 --> 17:33.785
WITH HER?

17:33.787 --> 17:37.188
I KNOW...
TONIGHT'S<i> OUR</i> NIGHT, ABBY,

17:37.190 --> 17:39.057
BUT SHE'S SAD AND LONELY.

17:39.059 --> 17:41.626
TOM'S GONE.

17:41.628 --> 17:44.128
JESS?
CAN YOU TAKE OUR PICTURE?

17:44.130 --> 17:45.530
IT'S ALL READY.
JUST SNAP.

17:45.532 --> 17:46.898
OKAY, GOT IT.

17:46.899 --> 17:48.265
THANKS FOR BEING
SUCH A GOOD SPORT.

17:48.268 --> 17:49.233
READY?

17:49.235 --> 17:50.535
GO ON,
STEP ON IN, DEAR.

17:50.536 --> 17:51.836
LET ME TAKE A PICTURE
OF THE WHOLE FAMILY.

17:51.838 --> 17:53.771
OH. OKAY, THANKS.
THERE YOU ARE.

17:53.773 --> 17:56.674
WE'RE<i> NOT</i> A FAMILY.

17:56.676 --> 17:58.609
COME ON, DAD.
LET'S GO FIND THE GAMES.

17:58.611 --> 17:59.610
THANK YOU.

17:59.612 --> 18:01.646
I'LL CATCH YOU LATER.

18:06.786 --> 18:08.486
[ BELL RINGS ]

18:08.488 --> 18:09.754
Ben: THEY WON'T STOP!

18:09.756 --> 18:10.721
GOT IT!

18:10.723 --> 18:12.690
WHICH ONE DID YOU GET?

18:12.692 --> 18:14.792
THAT GUY DOWN THERE
IS GONNA BEAT YOU.

18:14.794 --> 18:16.494
[ BELL DINGING ]

18:16.496 --> 18:18.296
CONGRATULATIONS,
LITTLE LADY.

18:18.298 --> 18:20.765
WINNER GETS TO PICK
A PRIZE!

18:20.767 --> 18:22.834
NICE, MONKEY!
[ LAUGHS ]

18:25.872 --> 18:27.338
WINNER!

18:27.340 --> 18:29.740
SHE'S HAVING A GOOD TIME.

18:29.742 --> 18:31.542
YEAH.

18:31.543 --> 18:33.343
THE SPLIT'S
BEEN TOUGH ON HER.

18:33.346 --> 18:35.680
SO HAS EVERYTHING ELSE.

18:37.817 --> 18:39.350
HOW ARE<i> YOU</i> DOING?

18:39.352 --> 18:41.786
IT'S HARD TO BE HAPPY.

18:43.389 --> 18:45.156
BUT THIS PLACE
IS HELPING.

18:45.158 --> 18:46.757
THANKS
FOR LETTING ME TAG ALONG.

18:46.759 --> 18:48.126
YEAH.

18:51.764 --> 18:53.431
WHAT'S WRONG?

18:54.434 --> 18:55.850
WHAT?

18:55.851 --> 18:57.267
THIS IS
GONNA SOUND CRAZY,

18:57.270 --> 18:59.837
BUT I-I-I THOUGHT
I SAW CORNELL OVER THERE.

18:59.839 --> 19:01.322
HERE?

19:01.323 --> 19:02.806
ON THE OTHER SIDE
OF THAT RIDE, YEAH.

19:02.809 --> 19:04.242
I DOUBT
SHE'D RISK COMING HERE.

19:04.244 --> 19:05.910
I MEAN, THAT ACTUALLY MEANS
SHE'D HAVE FUN.

19:05.912 --> 19:08.479
DAD?
CAN WE GET KETTLE CORN?

19:08.481 --> 19:10.882
"CAN WE GET
KETTLE CORN?"

19:10.884 --> 19:13.818
YOU KNOW
THE ANSWER.

19:13.820 --> 19:15.853
WE'LL WAIT RIGHT HERE
FOR YOU, OKAY?

19:15.855 --> 19:16.921
OKAY.

19:20.860 --> 19:23.928
YOU KNOW,
I APOLOGIZED TO CHRISTY,

19:23.930 --> 19:25.863
BUT NOT TO<i> YOU.</i>

19:25.865 --> 19:28.599
JESS, I WAS THERE, TOO.

19:28.601 --> 19:31.669
I GUESS I JUST FEEL
MORE GUILTY 'CAUSE...

19:31.671 --> 19:33.571
I DON'T REGRET IT.

19:35.175 --> 19:37.475
BECAUSE OF OUR MISTAKE,

19:37.477 --> 19:39.877
I MEAN, I HAD
FIVE BEAUTIFUL YEARS WITH TOM.

19:42.182 --> 19:44.515
YOU GAVE ME THAT.

19:44.517 --> 19:47.952
AND I'M ALWAYS
GONNA BE GRATEFUL FOR THAT.

19:49.322 --> 19:50.488
[ ABBY SCREAMS ]

19:51.558 --> 19:53.391
ABBY!
ABBY, WHAT'S WRONG?!

19:53.393 --> 19:54.692
WHAT HAPPENED, HON?

19:55.595 --> 19:56.827
WHAT HAPPENED?

20:01.901 --> 20:03.267
[ SOBBING ]

20:06.940 --> 20:09.874
HONEY, IT'S OKAY.

20:12.745 --> 20:15.379
EVERYTHING'S
GONNA BE OKAY.

20:15.381 --> 20:17.248
[ SOBBING ]

20:32.432 --> 20:34.732
CAN WE FIX IT?

20:34.734 --> 20:36.734
IT'S DEAD, MONK.

20:37.804 --> 20:41.272
MOM'S GONNA BE SO MAD.

20:41.274 --> 20:42.840
WHAT DO I DO?

20:42.842 --> 20:44.442
TELL HER THE TRUTH.

20:44.444 --> 20:46.611
SHE'LL BE ANGRY YOU DIDN'T
TAKE CARE OF YOUR PHONE,

20:46.613 --> 20:47.778
BUT SHE'LL GET OVER IT.

20:47.780 --> 20:49.447
YOU KNOW THAT.

20:51.417 --> 20:52.883
[ SIGHS ]
IT'S MY FAULT.

20:52.885 --> 20:55.419
I HAVE TO TAKE
RESPONSIBILITY.

20:55.421 --> 20:57.955
YES, YOU DO.

20:57.957 --> 20:59.924
YOU GOT TO FACE
THE MUSIC.

20:59.926 --> 21:02.526
AND SO WILL I
IF I DON'T GET YOU HOME SOON.

21:02.528 --> 21:04.929
I DON'T WANT TO GO
TO UNCLE MICHAEL'S HOUSE.

21:04.931 --> 21:05.930
I DON'T LIKE IT THERE.

21:05.932 --> 21:07.965
YOU USED TO LOVE IT.

21:07.967 --> 21:11.702
HE HAS ALL THE GAMES AND MOVIES
AND A BIG FLAT-SCREEN.

21:11.704 --> 21:14.672
[ Voice breaking ]
IT'S NOT HOME. I WANT
TO SLEEP IN MY OWN BED.

21:14.674 --> 21:16.507
PLEASE.

21:17.710 --> 21:19.477
YOU JUST GOT TO BE PATIENT,
SWEETIE.

21:19.479 --> 21:21.479
THAT'S ALL
I CAN TELL YOU.

21:23.349 --> 21:24.882
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

21:24.884 --> 21:26.517
Jess:
HEY, ARE YOU OKAY, ABBY?

21:26.519 --> 21:27.952
I GOT YOU
THE KETTLE CORN.

21:27.954 --> 21:29.287
LET'S JUST GO.

21:34.794 --> 21:36.894
Sam: TRUST ME --
THAT'S THE LAST TIME

21:36.896 --> 21:39.363
I GOT ROPED
INTO A BACHELOR AUCTION.

21:39.365 --> 21:41.465
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

21:42.869 --> 21:44.468
DETECTIVE CORNELL.

21:44.470 --> 21:48.072
I'M SORRY TO INTERRUPT.

21:48.808 --> 21:50.474
THIS IS
SAM MORRISON.

21:50.476 --> 21:52.376
HELLO.

21:52.378 --> 21:54.445
THAT'S A PRICY BORDEAUX.

21:54.447 --> 21:56.013
I LIKE IT.

22:03.690 --> 22:06.490
YOU TREAT YOURSELF WELL,
MR. MORRISON.

22:06.492 --> 22:09.894
THREE HOUSES, TWO CARS,
LOTS OF TRIPS OVERSEAS.

22:10.997 --> 22:13.030
W-WHY ARE YOU
CHECKING UP ON<i> ME?</i>

22:13.032 --> 22:15.666
I'M NOT IN THE MIDDLE
OF WHATEVER THIS IS.

22:15.668 --> 22:17.068
OH, THAT'S NOT ACCURATE.

22:18.237 --> 22:21.005
YOU WERE WITH MRS. CRAWFORD
THE NIGHT TOM MURPHY GOT KILLED.

22:21.007 --> 22:22.840
WHAT ARE YOU IMPLYING?

22:22.842 --> 22:24.875
I TOLD YOU
SAM WAS A GOOD FRIEND

22:24.877 --> 22:26.944
WHO GAVE ME
A SHOULDER TO CRY ON.

22:26.946 --> 22:28.079
RIGHT.

22:28.081 --> 22:29.780
AFTER YOU FOUND OUT

22:29.782 --> 22:32.783
THAT YOUR HUSBAND
HAD SLEPT WITH JESS MURPHY.

22:32.785 --> 22:35.519
THAT MUST HAVE BEEN
SO HARD TO HEAR.

22:35.521 --> 22:37.688
I HAD MY SUSPICIONS.

22:39.559 --> 22:42.827
SO, YOU LEFT THE HOUSE,
AND YOU WENT TO THE KWIK MART,

22:42.829 --> 22:45.529
AND THEN MR. MORRISON
OFFERED YOU COMFORT.

22:45.531 --> 22:46.897
I LISTENED.

22:46.899 --> 22:49.967
CHRISTY'S BEEN
IN ABSOLUTE HELL.

22:49.969 --> 22:51.836
HER HUSBAND'S A LIAR.

22:51.838 --> 22:54.772
IF YOU ASK ME,
THE GUY'S AN ASS.

22:55.842 --> 23:00.077
I'D RATHER ASK YOU WHAT TIME
MRS. CRAWFORD LEFT YOUR HOUSE.

23:00.079 --> 23:01.912
I LEFT AT 1:00.
12:3--

23:06.419 --> 23:08.652
IT WAS HALF PAST,
DETECTIVE.

23:08.654 --> 23:09.920
MM.

23:09.922 --> 23:11.055
ANYTHING ELSE?

23:11.057 --> 23:13.858
I KNOW WHERE TO FIND YOU
IF I NEED YOU.

23:13.860 --> 23:15.793
THANK YOU.

23:16.963 --> 23:18.462
SAM.

23:18.464 --> 23:19.964
I'M NOT DOING THIS.

23:30.576 --> 23:33.677
PEOPLE DO SHOW THEIR TRUE COLORS
WHEN THEY'RE UNDER PRESSURE.

23:35.948 --> 23:39.517
WHAT TIME DID YOU COME HOME
THE NIGHT TOM WAS KILLED?

23:52.465 --> 23:54.432
ISN'T THAT
DETECTIVE CORNELL'S CAR?

23:54.434 --> 23:56.500
YEAH.
WHAT'S SHE DOING HERE?

23:56.502 --> 23:57.635
THAT'S MOM'S BOY--

23:58.805 --> 24:00.204
SAM.

24:01.607 --> 24:03.073
HE'S MOM'S FRIEND.

24:03.075 --> 24:05.910
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

24:08.114 --> 24:10.581
I'LL BE BACK.

24:10.583 --> 24:12.716
[ IGNITION CHIMING ]

24:14.587 --> 24:15.853
[ CHIMING STOPS ]

24:15.855 --> 24:19.890
CAN YOU TALK TO MOM
SO WE CAN ALL COME HOME?

24:19.892 --> 24:22.993
YOUR MOTHER AND I
CAN'T LIVE TOGETHER ANYMORE.

24:22.995 --> 24:25.012
WELL...

24:25.013 --> 24:27.030
CAN YOU ASK HER
IF I CAN COME LIVE WITH<i> YOU?</i>

24:27.033 --> 24:28.833
I'LL HELP
TAKE CARE OF YOU, DAD.

24:28.835 --> 24:31.535
I CAN DO STUFF AROUND THE HOUSE.
YOU'LL SEE.

24:31.537 --> 24:34.071
IT'S NOT THAT SIMPLE.

24:34.073 --> 24:35.906
DON'T YOU WANT ME?

24:37.610 --> 24:40.478
OF COURSE I DO.

24:40.480 --> 24:45.015
BUT A GIRL NEEDS HER MOTHER --
ESPECIALLY A<i> TEENAGE</i> GIRL.

24:45.017 --> 24:47.184
YOU WANT TO BE
WITH JESS.

24:47.186 --> 24:49.553
YOU LOVE HER.

24:49.555 --> 24:52.823
ABBY, WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.
I LOVE YOU AND NAT.

24:52.825 --> 24:54.959
JESS IS JUST A FRIEND.

24:54.961 --> 24:57.261
MOM SAYS THE SAME THING
ABOUT SAM,

24:57.263 --> 24:59.029
BUT I SAW HER KISS HIM.

25:00.933 --> 25:02.933
PLEASE, DAD.

25:02.935 --> 25:05.669
I WANT TO LIVE WITH<i> YOU.</i>

25:05.671 --> 25:08.205
I WANT THAT, TOO, SWEETHEART,
BELIEVE ME.

25:08.207 --> 25:09.206
BUT --

25:09.208 --> 25:11.242
MOM'S RIGHT --
YOU'RE A LIAR.

25:11.244 --> 25:12.977
[ Voice breaking ]
YOU SAY YOU LOVE US,

25:12.979 --> 25:14.645
BUT YOU JUST WANT
TO BE WITH JESS.

25:19.952 --> 25:21.652
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

25:21.654 --> 25:23.687
[ SIGHS ]

25:25.758 --> 25:27.258
Christy:
THIS IS RIDICULOUS.

25:27.260 --> 25:28.859
I HAD NOTHING TO DO
WITH TOM'S DEATH.

25:28.861 --> 25:31.028
I'M NOT ACCUSING YOU,
MRS. CRAWFORD.

25:31.030 --> 25:33.964
IF THIS IS WHAT YOU DID TO BEN,
NO WONDER HE WENT NUTS.

25:33.966 --> 25:36.166
YOUR HUSBAND
WENT AND SLEPT WITH A NEIGHBOR.

25:36.168 --> 25:37.868
I'VE SEEN WOMEN
COMMIT MURDER

25:37.870 --> 25:39.837
FOR LESS
THAN WHAT YOU'VE BEEN THROUGH.

25:39.839 --> 25:41.038
YOU ARGUED.

25:41.040 --> 25:43.908
DIDN'T YOU SAY,
"JESS AND TOM MUST GO"?

25:43.910 --> 25:45.175
DID YOU SAY THAT?

25:45.177 --> 25:46.043
[ DOOR OPENS ]

25:46.045 --> 25:48.112
THAT'S NOT WHAT SHE SAID!

25:48.114 --> 25:50.648
YOU'RE GETTING IT
ALL WRONG!

25:50.650 --> 25:52.650
WHAT<i> DID</i> YOUR MOTHER SAY,
ABBY?

25:53.786 --> 25:56.987
SHE SAID SHE'D TAKE US
IF DAD DIDN'T GO AWAY.

25:57.990 --> 25:59.990
YOU HEARD THE FIGHT?

25:59.992 --> 26:01.325
<i> EVERYONE</i> HEARD
THE FIGHT, MOM.

26:01.327 --> 26:03.561
I'M SO SORRY.
YEAH, YOU'RE SORRY.

26:03.563 --> 26:05.996
YOU GUYS CAN'T KEEP DOING THIS.
ABBY'S JUST A KID.

26:07.934 --> 26:09.300
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

26:10.136 --> 26:12.136
SWEETHEART, COME HERE.

26:12.138 --> 26:14.171
COME HERE.

26:14.173 --> 26:16.206
WE'VE HAD ENOUGH.

26:23.849 --> 26:26.850
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M REALLY SORRY, HON.

26:34.260 --> 26:36.594
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

26:38.331 --> 26:39.863
[ SIGHS DEEPLY ]

26:39.865 --> 26:42.333
YOU OKAY?

26:43.836 --> 26:46.236
THERE'S JUST
TOO MUCH QUIET.

26:48.107 --> 26:50.174
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.

26:51.978 --> 26:54.178
I'LL WALK YOU HOME.

26:54.180 --> 26:57.014
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.
I'LL BE FINE.

27:00.620 --> 27:02.753
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

27:12.832 --> 27:14.898
YOU WANT TO TALK
OR...?

27:17.737 --> 27:18.936
FORGET IT. I'M SORR--

27:18.938 --> 27:20.521
NO.

27:20.522 --> 27:22.105
I'D<i> LOVE</i> SOME COMPANY.

27:24.977 --> 27:27.011
¶ OHH, OHH ¶

27:27.013 --> 27:30.948
¶ STAY CLOSE TO ME TONIGHT,
GIRL ¶

27:30.950 --> 27:36.020
¶ ONLY TO YOU
I WOULD REVEAL MY TEARS ¶

27:38.024 --> 27:41.959
¶ SO TELL THE POLICE
I AIN'T HOME TONIGHT ¶

27:41.961 --> 27:46.897
¶ MESSING AROUND WITH YOU
IS GONNA GET ME LIFE ¶

27:46.899 --> 27:49.400
¶ YEAH ¶

27:49.402 --> 27:50.834
¶ IF THIS IS THE KIND OF LOVE ¶

27:50.836 --> 27:53.671
¶ THAT MY MOM
USED TO WARN ME ABOUT ¶

27:53.673 --> 27:56.273
¶ MAN, I'M IN TROUBLE ¶

27:56.275 --> 28:00.044
¶ I'M IN REAL BIG TROUBLE ¶

28:00.046 --> 28:01.979
¶ IF THIS IS THE KIND OF LOVE ¶

28:01.981 --> 28:04.882
¶ THAT THE OLD FOLKS
USED TO WARN ME ABOUT ¶

28:04.884 --> 28:07.818
¶ MAN, I'M IN TROUBLE ¶

28:07.820 --> 28:10.454
¶ I'M IN REAL BIG TROUBLE ¶

28:14.360 --> 28:16.260
GOOD MORNING.

28:16.262 --> 28:18.195
MM.

28:18.197 --> 28:21.799
LAST NIGHT WAS INSANE.

28:21.801 --> 28:23.267
GOOD OR BAD?

28:23.269 --> 28:24.835
GREAT.

28:24.837 --> 28:27.137
BUT IT WASN'T AS GOOD
AS LAST TIME.

28:27.139 --> 28:28.238
HEY.

28:28.240 --> 28:29.740
[ CHUCKLES ]

28:29.742 --> 28:31.775
I DIDN'T MEAN IT
LIKE THAT.

28:31.777 --> 28:33.877
IT'S JUST...

28:33.879 --> 28:35.412
[ SIGHS ]

28:35.414 --> 28:37.915
LAST TIME, WE MADE TOM.

28:45.057 --> 28:47.991
I CAN'T IMAGINE
HOW HARD THAT'S BEEN FOR YOU.

28:50.930 --> 28:54.398
TOM WAS SUCH A GREAT KID.

28:56.268 --> 28:58.235
WE COULD MAKE ANOTHER.

29:01.974 --> 29:03.373
WHAT?

29:04.810 --> 29:05.809
I'M SORRY.

29:05.811 --> 29:08.145
UM...THAT WAS...

29:10.049 --> 29:12.950
I SHOULDN'T HAVE SAID THAT.
JUST IGNORE THAT I SAID THAT.

29:12.952 --> 29:14.752
UM...

29:14.754 --> 29:17.154
I JUST MISS TOM
SO MUCH LATELY,

29:17.156 --> 29:20.524
I DON'T KNOW WHAT I'M SAYING,
SO IF YOU COULD JUST REWIND...

29:20.526 --> 29:23.393
IT'S OKAY.
DON'T WORRY ABOUT IT.

29:24.930 --> 29:26.430
I'M GONNA
JUMP IN THE SHOWER.

29:33.472 --> 29:35.973
[ SHOWER WATER RUNNING ]

29:39.979 --> 29:41.044
[ THUD ]

30:09.809 --> 30:11.875
[ SHOWER WATER RUNNING ]

30:40.272 --> 30:42.005
[ WATER SHUTS OFF ]

30:50.616 --> 30:52.583
YOU'RE DRESSED.
YEP.

30:52.585 --> 30:55.619
WELL, I WAS KIND OF,
SORT OF HOPING YOU'D JOIN ME.

30:55.621 --> 30:58.956
UH...
CAN I GET A RAIN CHECK?

30:58.958 --> 31:00.390
[ MOANING ]

31:00.392 --> 31:03.126
OR WE COULD...
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:03.128 --> 31:06.997
YEAH, I JUST, UM, I-I GOT
A TON TO DO THIS MORNING.

31:06.999 --> 31:09.166
ARE YOU SURE?

31:09.168 --> 31:11.368
YEAH. I'M SORRY.

31:11.370 --> 31:14.605
NO, NO, NO. BUT M-M-MAYBE
WE CAN MAKE IT UP LATER.

31:14.607 --> 31:17.074
OKAY. YEAH.

31:17.076 --> 31:20.077
MAYBE I CAN MAKE SOMETHING
FOR DINNER.

31:20.079 --> 31:21.345
THAT SOUNDS GREAT.

31:49.642 --> 31:50.941
I'M NOT READY FOR YOU YET.

31:50.943 --> 31:53.443
JUST GIVE ME
WHAT YOU HAVE SO FAR.

31:53.445 --> 31:54.978
YOU KNOW
I CAN'T DO THAT.

31:54.980 --> 31:56.246
THE CLOCK IS TICKING.

31:56.248 --> 31:58.649
AND THIS IS NEW EVIDENCE
I FOUND FOR YOU.

31:58.651 --> 32:01.285
SO LET ME PROCESS IT --
FOR<i> YOU.</i>

32:01.287 --> 32:03.287
WHEN CAN I HAVE
MY RESULTS?

32:03.289 --> 32:05.422
WHEN I'M DONE.

32:10.062 --> 32:12.462
[ KEYBOARD CLACKING ]

33:03.716 --> 33:06.550
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

33:07.686 --> 33:08.685
[ SIGHS ]

33:08.687 --> 33:10.620
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

33:10.622 --> 33:11.755
WHAT IS IT?

33:11.757 --> 33:13.090
ABBY: Daddy?

33:13.092 --> 33:15.058
HEY, MONKEY.

33:15.060 --> 33:16.560
What's up?

33:16.561 --> 33:18.061
I'M SORRY
I YELLED AT YOU.

33:18.063 --> 33:19.997
I'M SORRY, TOO.

33:19.999 --> 33:22.499
I ASKED MOM
IF WE COULD COME HOME.

33:22.501 --> 33:24.101
SHE SAID NO.

33:24.102 --> 33:25.702
OH, IT'S OKAY. W-WE'RE GONNA
FIGURE IT OUT, ALL RIGHT?

33:25.704 --> 33:27.471
OKAY.

33:27.473 --> 33:30.007
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

33:32.211 --> 33:34.611
HEY, SWEETIE,
DO YOU KNOW WHERE NAT KEPT

33:34.613 --> 33:36.413
the key to Jess' house?

33:36.415 --> 33:37.815
WHY?

33:37.816 --> 33:39.216
Well,
we don't need it anymore,

33:39.218 --> 33:42.386
AND, UH, JESS' SISTER
ASKED FOR IT BACK.

33:42.388 --> 33:45.022
I DON'T KNOW.
MAYBE IN THE KITCHEN.

33:45.024 --> 33:47.024
YEAH?

33:47.026 --> 33:49.226
This place is boring.
It's not fun.

33:49.228 --> 33:51.061
There's nothing to do here.

33:51.063 --> 33:54.131
Uncle Michael keeps trying
to teach me how to play chess.

33:54.133 --> 33:57.100
WELL, CHESS IS
A GOOD GAME TO KNOW.

33:57.102 --> 33:58.668
I DON'T WANT TO PLAY CHESS.

33:58.670 --> 34:01.438
It's like
joining the math club.

34:01.440 --> 34:03.073
YEAH, I DON'T BLAME YOU.
CHESS IS BORING.

34:03.075 --> 34:06.043
Um...is it okay

34:06.045 --> 34:07.744
IF I GIVE YOU A CALL BACK
A LITTLE LATER?

34:07.746 --> 34:08.745
Okay.

34:08.747 --> 34:10.113
ALL RIGHT.
I LOVE YOU.

34:10.115 --> 34:11.748
[ Click, dial tone ]

34:11.750 --> 34:13.517
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

35:14.546 --> 35:15.612
Jess: PUT THAT DOWN.

35:18.884 --> 35:20.717
JESS,
WHAT HAPPENED TO JANE?

35:20.719 --> 35:21.818
WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?

35:21.820 --> 35:23.420
I KNOW ABOUT THE PILLS.

35:23.422 --> 35:25.755
I KNOW
THAT YOU'RE NOT TAKING THEM.

35:25.757 --> 35:27.691
THAT BLUE JACKET'S YOURS.

35:27.693 --> 35:29.626
WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

35:29.628 --> 35:31.128
JESS, YOUR BABY IS DEAD.

35:31.130 --> 35:32.829
WHAT ARE THE ODDS
OF HAVING TWO DEAD KIDS?

35:35.167 --> 35:36.466
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE.

35:36.468 --> 35:38.335
WHAT HAPPENED
TO THEM BOTH?

35:38.337 --> 35:39.736
WHAT HAPPENED TO THEM?

35:39.738 --> 35:41.304
WHAT DID YOU DO TO THEM?

35:41.306 --> 35:42.472
I LOVED MY KIDS!

35:42.474 --> 35:43.840
GET OUT!

35:43.842 --> 35:45.375
I HATE YOU!

35:46.145 --> 35:48.678
YOU DON'T KNOW WHAT IT'S LIKE
TO LOSE A CHILD!

35:48.680 --> 35:50.347
I LOVED TOM, TOO!

35:51.283 --> 35:53.183
YOU STILL HAVE YOURS!

35:55.154 --> 35:57.154
[ PANTING ]

36:02.761 --> 36:04.895
[ LOCK CLICKS ]

36:12.738 --> 36:14.471
[ DIALING ]

36:14.473 --> 36:17.474
[ Ringing ]

36:17.476 --> 36:18.708
DAVE: Speak.

36:18.710 --> 36:19.709
911, MAN.

36:19.711 --> 36:21.328
WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY,
SIR?

36:21.329 --> 36:22.946
I THINK I GOT, LIKE,
A "FATAL ATTRACTION" THING

36:22.948 --> 36:24.214
HAPPENING WITH JESS MURPHY.

36:24.216 --> 36:25.815
WHAT?!

36:25.817 --> 36:27.784
HOLD ON.
YOU HIT THAT<i> AGAIN?</i>

36:27.786 --> 36:30.587
THAT'S NOT THE ISSUE.
H-HER BEING CRAZY IS THE ISSUE.

36:30.589 --> 36:32.956
YEAH. NO. WAIT.
UM, WHO'S THE CRAZY ONE, BEN?

36:32.958 --> 36:34.925
<i> SHE</i> IS. SERIOUSLY.

36:34.927 --> 36:36.777
SHE NEEDS MEDICATION.

36:36.778 --> 36:38.628
I SAW A PICTURE OF HER
WEARING THE BLUE JACKET.

36:38.630 --> 36:40.297
UH,<i> THE</i> BLUE JACKET?
THAT'S CRAZY.

36:40.299 --> 36:41.498
WHAT ARE YOU
GOING TO DO?

36:41.500 --> 36:42.666
THIS TIME,
I'M GONNA FIND IT.

36:42.668 --> 36:43.900
No, no, no, no, no,
no, no, no.

36:43.902 --> 36:45.435
DID WE LEARN<i> NOTHING</i>

36:45.436 --> 36:46.969
FROM POINTING FINGERS
AT PEOPLE, BENJAMIN?

36:46.972 --> 36:49.239
That's why...

36:49.241 --> 36:50.707
I'M GONNA GO
TALK TO HER SISTER FIRST.

36:50.709 --> 36:52.742
WELL, NICOLE SHOULD BE
AT YOGA.

36:52.744 --> 36:55.212
HER ASHTANGA CLASS
STARTS IN 20 MINUTES.

36:55.214 --> 36:56.680
HOW -- HOW THE HELL
WOULD YOU KNOW THAT?

36:56.682 --> 36:59.950
THE, UH, THE ZEN YOGA IS RIGHT
ACROSS FROM THE COLD STONE.

36:59.952 --> 37:01.851
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

37:01.853 --> 37:03.920
BEN?

37:04.790 --> 37:06.323
HI, SWEETIE.

37:10.963 --> 37:13.964
[ RELAXING MUSIC PLAYS ]

37:15.901 --> 37:18.268
WHAT DO YOU WANT, BEN?
I HAVE A CLASS.

37:18.270 --> 37:20.337
I WANT TO KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO JANE.

37:22.774 --> 37:24.641
SHE TOLD YOU ABOUT HER?

37:24.643 --> 37:26.610
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

37:26.612 --> 37:28.311
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

37:28.313 --> 37:29.813
HOW DID SHE DIE?

37:31.283 --> 37:33.950
SUDDEN INFANT DEATH SYNDROME.

37:33.952 --> 37:36.853
IT HAPPENS SOMETIMES.
BABIES JUST DIE FOR NO REASON.

37:36.855 --> 37:37.921
SIDS?

37:39.391 --> 37:40.857
JESS FELL APART.

37:40.859 --> 37:43.360
SCOTT HAD TO COMMIT HER
FOR 72 HOURS

37:43.362 --> 37:45.028
SO SHE WOULDN'T HURT
HERSELF.

37:46.698 --> 37:48.665
WAS SHE TAKING THESE
AT THE TIME?

37:48.667 --> 37:50.767
GO HOME, BEN.

37:50.768 --> 37:52.868
YOU SAID THAT I DIDN'T KNOW HER,
SO WHAT AM I MISSING?

37:52.871 --> 37:54.671
JESS IS BIPOLAR
AND GOES OFF HER MEDS

37:54.673 --> 37:56.606
AND HAPPENS TO HAVE
TWO DEAD CHILDREN?

37:56.608 --> 37:59.576
JESS DIDN'T KILL ANYBODY.

37:59.578 --> 38:02.145
WHAT'S WRONG WITH YOU?

38:02.146 --> 38:04.713
SHE HAS GOT<i> HUNDREDS</i> OF THESE
STASHED AWAY.

38:04.716 --> 38:07.984
YEAH, BECAUSE WHEN JESS
TAKES HER MEDS, SHE'S GREAT.

38:07.986 --> 38:09.519
SHE'S SO GOOD
THAT SHE FEELS

38:09.521 --> 38:10.920
LIKE SHE DOESN'T NEED THEM
ANYMORE.

38:10.922 --> 38:12.555
YEAH, WELL,
SHE'S NOT ON THEM NOW.

38:12.557 --> 38:13.957
HOW VIOLENT DOES SHE GET?

38:13.959 --> 38:15.892
IT'S NOT WHAT YOU THINK.

38:15.894 --> 38:18.828
WHEN JESS LOSES CONTROL,
SHE HAS FITS.

38:18.830 --> 38:22.365
SHE DESTROYS<i> THINGS,</i>
NOT PEOPLE.

38:22.367 --> 38:24.434
SCOTT COULDN'T TAKE
HER UPS AND DOWNS ANYMORE.

38:24.436 --> 38:26.203
THAT'S WHY HE LEFT.

38:26.204 --> 38:27.971
JESS SHOWED ME A VIDEO. SHE SAID
SCOTT DESTROYED THE HOUSE.

38:27.973 --> 38:29.439
IT WAS<i> HER,</i> WASN'T IT?

38:31.343 --> 38:33.410
SHE HAS OUTBURSTS.

38:33.412 --> 38:36.746
I'VE BEEN DEALING WITH IT
SINCE WE WERE TEENAGERS.

38:36.748 --> 38:39.449
BUT THERE'S NO WAY
THAT SHE KILLED TOM.

38:39.451 --> 38:41.851
SHE LOVED HIM
MORE THAN ANYTHING.

38:41.853 --> 38:44.354
DID YOU TELL CORNELL
ANY OF THIS?

38:46.792 --> 38:48.892
SHE'S MY SISTER.

39:09.614 --> 39:11.114
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

39:11.116 --> 39:12.582
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

39:12.584 --> 39:13.583
HELLO?

39:13.585 --> 39:15.051
I-IS SHE THERE?
Who?

39:15.053 --> 39:16.086
ABBY.

39:16.088 --> 39:17.921
Is Abby with you?

39:17.923 --> 39:19.055
WHAT? NO.

39:19.057 --> 39:20.056
[ Sobbing ] OH, GOD.

39:20.058 --> 39:21.624
Christy, what's going on?

39:21.626 --> 39:23.059
She was in her room.

39:23.061 --> 39:24.711
I WENT IN
TO CHECK ON HER,

39:24.712 --> 39:26.362
AND -- AND I THOUGHT
MAYBE SHE SNUCK OUT TO SEE YOU.

39:26.365 --> 39:28.398
ALL RIGHT,
I'M HEADED HOME NOW.

39:28.400 --> 39:29.666
How long
has she been gone?

39:29.668 --> 39:30.800
I'VE LOOKED EVERYWHERE,
BEN.

39:30.802 --> 39:32.869
She's -- She's gone.

39:32.871 --> 39:36.439
[ ENGINE REVS ]

39:36.441 --> 39:37.974
ABBY?!

39:39.845 --> 39:41.077
ABBY?!

39:44.116 --> 39:46.049
ABBY?!

39:55.894 --> 39:57.694
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

39:59.531 --> 40:02.031
JOHN PATRICK CALLED.
HE HAS RESULTS FOR YOU.

40:04.903 --> 40:06.002
ABBY?!

40:09.408 --> 40:11.641
ABBY?!

40:12.878 --> 40:13.977
ABBY?!

40:13.979 --> 40:15.779
[ PANTING ]

40:15.781 --> 40:17.647
ELAINE! ELAINE!

40:17.649 --> 40:18.882
ELAINE,
HAVE YOU SEEN ABBY?

40:18.884 --> 40:21.017
NO. WHAT'S GOING ON?
SHE'S MISSING.

40:29.161 --> 40:30.927
HAPPY NEW YEAR, ANDREA.

40:30.929 --> 40:31.961
HOW LONG'S SHE BEEN GONE?

40:31.963 --> 40:33.963
[ GASPS ] I DON'T KNOW.

40:39.004 --> 40:40.837
CALL DETECTIVE CORNELL.

40:46.178 --> 40:47.444
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

40:47.446 --> 40:48.745
[ DOORKNOB RATTLES ]

40:48.747 --> 40:49.946
DO YOU HAVE ABBY
IN THERE?!

40:49.948 --> 40:51.815
YOU LOST YOUR DAUGHTER
NOW?

40:51.817 --> 40:53.850
FEELS HORRIBLE,
DOESN'T IT?

40:53.852 --> 40:56.019
IF YOU HURT HER,
I'LL KILL YOU!

40:58.990 --> 41:00.490
[ SIGHS ]

41:00.492 --> 41:02.859
I WAS RIGHT.

41:02.861 --> 41:04.727
IT WAS<i> HER.</i>

41:04.729 --> 41:06.830
SHE KILLED TOM MURPHY.
